# Windsurf Rules

## ⛔ FILESYSTEM — ABSOLUTE PROHIBITION · READ THIS FIRST · EVERY TIME

**The agent generates garbage. This rule exists to stop it.**

Before creating ANY file, answer:
> "Will this file be a permanent part of the project after this task is done?"
> **NO → `tmp/` only → delete in same session. NOT ROOT. NOT src/. NOT ANYWHERE ELSE.**

### Files the agent MUST NEVER create outside tmp/:

```
Scripts:    fix.py fix.ts run.py run.ts debug.py debug.ts check.py try.py setup.py
            seed.ts migrate.py cleanup.py reset.py main_temp.py server_test.ts
Reports:    report.md report.json analysis.md output.md results.json summary.md
            notes.md notes.txt todo.md plan.md diff.txt log.txt error.log
Duplicates: file_v2.py file_old.ts file_new.py file_backup.ts file2.py index_new.ts
            component_v2.tsx service_old.py utils_new.ts model_backup.py *_copy.*
Docs:       NOTES.md CHANGES.md TODO.md PLAN.md TASKS.md PROGRESS.md GUIDE.md
            SETUP.md HOW_TO.md INSTRUCTIONS.md IDEAS.md DESIGN.md ARCHITECTURE.md
Data:       data.json dump.sql export.json import.json sample.json mock_data.py
            fixtures.json test_data.json fake_data.ts seed_data.json
```

### The only right answers:

| Agent wants to... | Must do instead |
|---|---|
| Create `fix.py` in root | `tmp/fix.py` → run → **delete** |
| Write `report.md` | Print in chat. **Never write to file.** |
| Create `notes.md` | Update `docs/CONTEXT.md` |
| Create `service_v2.py` | Edit `service.py` directly. Git is the backup. |
| Create `index_new.ts` | Edit `index.ts` directly. |
| Write `data.json` | `tmp/data.json` → use → **delete** |
| Output analysis | Print in chat. **Never write to file.** |

### tmp/ — the only quarantine zone:

```
tmp/
  .gitignore   ← contains exactly one line: *
  .gitkeep
```

**Cleanup is MANDATORY at the end of every task — not optional:**
```bash
find tmp/ -not -name '.gitignore' -not -name '.gitkeep' -not -type d -delete
```
Task is **NOT DONE** until this runs and returns empty.

### Root scan — run at START and END of every session:

```bash
find . -maxdepth 3 \
  -not -path '*/node_modules/*' -not -path '*/.git/*' -not -path '*/tmp/*' \
  \( -name '*_old.*' -o -name '*_new.*' -o -name '*_v2.*' -o -name '*_backup.*' \
     -o -name 'debug.*' -o -name 'fix.*' -o -name 'run.*' -o -name 'notes.*' \
     -o -name 'report.*' -o -name 'output.*' -o -name 'results.*' \
     -o -name 'data.json' -o -name 'dump.*' -o -name 'analysis.*' \) 2>/dev/null

find . -maxdepth 3 -name '*.md' \
  -not -name 'README.md' -not -path '*/docs/*' \
  -not -path '*/node_modules/*' -not -path '*/.git/*' 2>/dev/null
```

Anything found → **delete immediately** → log in checklist.

### Allowed .md files — complete whitelist, nothing else:

```
docs/SPEC.md        ← requirements, user stories, glossary
docs/ROADMAP.md     ← milestones, definition of done, current status
docs/STRUCTURE.md   ← directory tree, naming conventions, import rules
docs/DEPLOY.md      ← deployment targets, CI/CD, rollback
docs/DECISIONS.md   ← append-only architectural decisions log
docs/CONTEXT.md     ← overwritten each session: current state, next task
docs/FULL_RULES.md  ← full project rules reference
README.md           ← project root ONLY — single standard exception
```

**Every `.md` outside `docs/` (except `README.md`) = structural violation. Delete immediately.**
**Every `.md` inside `docs/` must stay current throughout development. Stale doc = broken doc.**

### Every response ends with this — non-negotiable:

```
ROOT SCAN : root ✓/✗ | sub-roots ✓/✗ | found+deleted: [exact list or —]
FILESYSTEM: tmp/ empty ✓/✗ | cleanup ran ✓/✗ | deleted this session: [exact list or —]
```

