## CONFIG CENTER — ONE PLACE, ONE TRUTH, NO EXCEPTIONS

**Absolute rule:** `config/` at project root is the ONLY place in the entire project
where constants and general-purpose variables are defined.
`src/`, `app/`, `services/`, `components/` — contain ONLY imports. Never values. Never literals.

```
config/        ← THE ONLY PLACE with values (single source of truth)
  index.ts     ← single re-export: import { API, AUTH, UI } from "@config"
  env.ts       ← ALL env vars: process.env.VAR || CONFIG_DEFAULTS.VAR
  defaults.ts  ← all default fallback values
  api.ts  auth.ts  ui.ts  limits.ts  routes.ts  regex.ts  http.ts  events.ts

src/ app/ services/ components/  ← references ONLY, never definitions
```

What belongs in config/ — everything used by more than one file:
API URLs, timeouts, auth keys, TTLs, pagination, breakpoints, routes,
regex, HTTP codes, event names, file limits, log levels, feature flags, i18n locales.
**When in doubt → config/. Default is always config/.**

.env priority — always `||`, never hardcode:
```typescript
// config/env.ts
export const ENV = {
  API_BASE_URL:   process.env.API_BASE_URL   || CONFIG_DEFAULTS.API_BASE_URL,
  API_TIMEOUT_MS: process.env.API_TIMEOUT_MS || CONFIG_DEFAULTS.API_TIMEOUT_MS,
  DATABASE_URL:   process.env.DATABASE_URL   || "",  // secret: no fallback
  JWT_SECRET:     process.env.JWT_SECRET     || "",  // secret: no fallback
} as const;
["DATABASE_URL","JWT_SECRET"].forEach(k => {
  if (!ENV[k]) throw new Error(`Missing required env var: ${k}`)
});
```

Rules:
- Found a value defined in src/ → bug, move to config/
- Found same value in two places → DRY violation, consolidate to config/
- New constant → config/ first, then import via `@config`
- Secrets: empty fallback + fail-fast at startup, never a real default
- Derived values reference base: `MAX_BYTES: LIMITS.MAX_FILE_SIZE_MB * 1024 * 1024`

