## CODE PRINCIPLES — ENFORCED ALWAYS

**Thin modules — default shape of all code:**
- One module = one responsibility. "And" in description → split it
- Max ~150 lines per file, max 30 lines per function, max 3 nesting levels
- Max 5 branches (cyclomatic complexity) per function — more → split
- No God objects/modules. No barrel files re-exporting 50+ things
- New team member must understand any module within 5 minutes

**Simplicity first:**
- DRY: zero duplicated logic or type structures — extract, reuse, inherit
- KISS: simplest solution that works, explainable in one sentence
- SOLID: one responsibility, extend don't modify, inject dependencies
- YAGNI: never implement for future use — requirements must exist today
- No premature optimization — measure first, optimize only what's proven slow
- Clever code is rejected — if it needs a comment to explain, rewrite it
- No magic literals — every string/number/regex → config/

**Async-first — I/O is always async, sync is the exception:**
```typescript
// ✗ VIOLATION — sync blocks event loop
fs.readFileSync(), execSync(), db.querySync()

// ✓ CORRECT — always async
await fs.promises.readFile(), await db.query()
```
```python
# ✗ VIOLATION — blocks event loop
time.sleep(), requests.get(), open()

# ✓ CORRECT
await asyncio.sleep(), await httpx.get(), await aiofiles.open()
```
Rules:
- Every function touching I/O (DB, file, network, cache) must be async
- Never use sync sleep — always async sleep
- DB drivers must be async-native (asyncpg, prisma, sqlalchemy async)
- HTTP clients must be async (httpx/aiohttp for Python, fetch for Node)
- CPU-bound work > ~10ms → offload to worker thread / executor
- Sync block in async context → annotate `// SYNC-BLOCK: reason` + refactor ASAP

**Strict typing — zero tolerance:**
- No any / @ts-ignore / implicit types — strict mode always
- Types: extend/Partial/Pick/Omit/mapped — never duplicate field structures
- domain.ts is type root — all other types derive from it

**Quality gates — every commit and deploy:**
- Pre-commit: prettier → eslint (0 warnings) → tsc/mypy (0 errors) + unit tests — BLOCKS commit
- CI on PR: full test suite (≥90% line / ≥85% branch / ≥95% fn) — BLOCKS merge
- Pre-deploy: full PRE-PRODUCTION TEST PROGRAM (10 phases) — BLOCKS deploy
- No --no-verify bypasses. No "fix after deploy". Quality is continuous, not a phase.

