## TESTING — 90%+ COVERAGE · MANDATORY AT EVERY COMMIT AND DEPLOY

Every function, class, and API endpoint ships with tests. No code without tests.

**Coverage thresholds — enforced by CI, blocks merge and deploy:**
```
Lines:      ≥ 90%
Branches:   ≥ 85%
Functions:  ≥ 95%
Statements: ≥ 90%
```

**Every function must be tested with ALL of:**
```
✓ Happy path — valid input → expected output
✓ Boundary values — min, max, zero, empty string, empty array
✓ Null / undefined / None input
✓ At least 2 negative cases → expected error / exception
✓ Async: resolved value + rejected promise + timeout (if async)
```

**Every class must be tested with ALL of:**
```
✓ Constructor — valid args, missing required, invalid args
✓ Every public method — happy path + ≥1 negative case
✓ State transitions — object state changes correctly
✓ Error states — called in wrong order, on disposed object
```

**Negative test matrix — mandatory coverage:**
```
Empty / null / undefined input       → always
Boundary violations (max+1, min-1)   → always
Missing required fields              → always
Invalid format (email, uuid, date)   → always
Not found (non-existent id)          → always for CRUD
Unauthorized access                  → always for protected ops
Dependency failure (DB down, timeout)→ always for I/O ops
Duplicate data (already exists)      → always for create ops
```

**Integration tests — required for:**
```
✓ Every API endpoint (request → service → DB → response)
✓ Every service method touching DB (real test DB, rollback per test)
✓ Every auth flow (register, login, refresh, logout, protected route)
✓ Every background job / worker
```

**Test naming — executable documentation:**
```typescript
// ✗ it("works") / it("error case") / it("test1")
// ✓ it("throws ValidationError when email format is invalid")
// ✓ it("returns 401 when authorization header is missing")
// ✓ it("rolls back transaction when second insert fails")
```

**Forbidden — invalidates coverage:**
```typescript
it.skip(...)           // forbidden in committed code
expect(true).toBe(true)// meaningless assertion — rejected
/* istanbul ignore */  // forbidden without documented reason + issue link
```

**Execution per stage:**
```
pre-commit:  unit tests only       (~30s) — BLOCKS commit on failure
pre-push/CI: full suite + coverage  — BLOCKS merge if thresholds not met
pre-deploy:  unit + integration + e2e — BLOCKS deploy on any failure
```

Test file mirrors source: `src/services/user.ts` → `tests/services/user.service.test.ts`



