## PRODUCTION BUILD — MINIMUM BYTES, MAXIMUM RESULT

Every byte deployed costs money. Production = smallest artifact with full functionality.

**Production bundle contains ONLY:**
- compiled + minified + tree-shaken application code
- runtime dependencies (never devDependencies)
- compressed static assets (hashed filenames)
- README.md — the single documentation file

**Production bundle NEVER contains:**
```
src/  tests/  docs/  tmp/  .github/  .vscode/  .git/
*.spec.* *.test.* *.stories.*  *.md (except README.md)
tsconfig.json  .eslintrc  .prettierrc  jest/vitest configs
.env.* files  Dockerfile  docker-compose.yml  lockfiles
coverage/  logs/  node_modules devDependencies
```

**Bundle size targets:**
```
Frontend initial JS:   < 100kb gzip
Per-route lazy chunk:  < 50kb gzip
Total CSS:             < 20kb gzip
Docker Node.js image:  < 150MB
Docker Python image:   < 200MB
```

**Tree-shaking — always specific imports:**
```typescript
// ✗ import _ from "lodash"          — ships entire 70kb library
// ✓ import { debounce } from "lodash-es"  — ships ~2kb
// ✗ import moment from "moment"     — 67kb gzip
// ✓ import { format } from "date-fns"     — ~2kb per function
```

**Multi-stage Dockerfile — mandatory for every service:**
```dockerfile
FROM node:20-alpine AS builder
# ... install all deps + build

FROM node:20-alpine AS production
COPY --from=builder /app/dist ./dist
COPY --from=builder /app/node_modules/prod-only ./node_modules
COPY README.md ./
USER node                    # never run as root
CMD ["node", "dist/main.js"] # no src/, no tests/, no docs/
```

**.dockerignore — mandatory, excludes everything not needed in build context:**
Always present. Excludes: .git, node_modules, tests/, docs/, *.md(!README), 
.env.*, IDE configs, CI configs, tmp/, logs/, coverage/

**Before every deploy — verify:**
```bash
docker image ls   # check image size
npx depcheck      # find unused dependencies
npm audit         # zero high/critical CVEs
npx vite-bundle-visualizer  # no chunk > 200kb uncompressed
```

